ia.org/wiki/Horace_Dutton_Taft","primary_url_label":"Wikipedia"},"narrative_blocks":[{"header":"He founded The Taft School","body":"Horace Dutton Taft opened a college preparatory school in Pelham Manor, New York in 1890, moved it to Watertown, Connecticut in 1893, and served as headmaster for 46 years. When he retired in 1936, Time called him 'the grandest' of prep school headmasters. He continued teaching civics until his death in 1943 at age 81.","number":1},{"header":"As a boy he met Sherman and Grant","body":"Horace Dutton Taft's 1942 memoir Memories and Opinions records a childhood trip to Washington where his mother introduced him to General Sherman and President Grant. Sherman was 'spry and chatty and joked with his father, who was then Secretary of War.' Grant 'was about as cheerful and communicative as a tombstone.' On the way home at the 1876 Philadelphia Centennial, he saw an early telephone demonstration. Some people, he was told, foolishly believed 'we should soon be able to talk all over town.'","number":2}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"civic_peer","related_id":"HD1395","display_label":"His father co-founded Skull and Bones with this man — Horace joined the same society a generation later.","link_text":"William Huntington Russell"}],"bio":{"display_name":"Horace Dutton Taft","first_name":"Horace","last_name":"Taft","married_names":[],"middle_name":"Dutton"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"horace-taft-1861"}},"burialCemetery":{"id":"CEM087","name":"Evergreen Cemetery","city":"Watertown","county":"Litchfield County","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States","lat":41.6001,"lng":-73.1193,"visitable":true,"hooker_connections":["HD3103","HD3105","X02080","X02085","I00744","HD4416","HD4420","I00748","I00745"]},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}